	    			<h2 class="headContent"> Plan Ahead</h2>
				<p class="tipContent"> Consider your current
				abilities from your recent training to determine
				how much of a hike you can handle, be
				realistic. Get a rough idea of how
				many hours you want to hike, how far you can go,
				what hiking supply load you need, and then use
				maps and guidebooks to find a trail that matches
				your desires and abilities. Make sure you know the terrain
				you will be hiking in and dress accordingly. Also make sure to
				bring a map along with you. Check any fees or permits that you need to purchase ahead of time. Also remember to double check the weather, especially during the winter months.  </p>
